data.title: The Governor General of Canada
data.text:
Awarded on: December 15, 2015

Paul Nguyen has put in hundreds of hours over the past 11 years to eliminate racial discrimination through Jane-Finch.com, a youth-led volunteer forum that aims to generate co-operation, civic engagement and positive imagery associated with the Jane and Finch neighbourhood in Toronto. In addition, he is also a volunteer board member of the National Ethnic Press and Media Council of Canada, where he helps to raise the profile of ethnic broadcasters and print publications in Canada for a younger generation.
